{"lemma":"ما","slug":"ما","root":"م.#","root_slug":"م-_","root_link":"/words/roots/م-_","pos":null,"pos_camel":"pron_rel","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ما","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2565},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adv","conj","particle","pron"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43475",""],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D8%A7"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"pron","gloss":"what?","tags":["interrogative"]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"some, a certain","tags":["indefinite"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱللّٰهَ لَا يَسْتَحْيِي أَنْ يَضْرِبَ مَثَلًا مَا بَعُوضَةً فَمَا فَوْقَهَا","english":"Indeed, God is not timid to present an example: that of a mosquito or what is smaller than it."}]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"that which, what","tags":["relative"],"examples":[{"text":"اِقْرَأْ مَا كَتَبْتُ.","english":"Read what I wrote."},{"text":"مَا تَفْعَلُ تُجَازَى عَلَيْهِ","english":"Whatever you do, you are paid back for it."}]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"whichever; whatever","examples":[{"text":"مَا تَفْعَلْ تُجَازَ عَلَيْهِ","english":"Whatever you do, you will be paid back for it."},{"text":"مَا نَنْسَخْ مِنْ آيَةٍ أَوْ نُنْسِهَا نَأْتِ بِخَيْرٍ مِنْهَا أَوْ مِثْلِهَا","english":"Whatever we abrogate that is a passage or make people forget, we come up with others that are better than or just like it."}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"not; never","examples":[{"text":"See also: لَا, لَمْ, لَنْ, and لَيْسَ"},{"text":"وَطَرٌ مَا فِيهِ مِنْ عَيْبٍ سِوَى – أَنَّهُ مَرَّ كَلَمْحِ ٱلْبَصَرِ","english":"The wish that is without a mistake except that it passed like a glance of the eye."}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"as long as","examples":[{"text":"فَمَا ٱسْتَقَامُوا لَكُمْ فَٱسْتَقِيمُوا لَهُمْ","english":"So as long as they are straight with you, be straight with them."}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"A subordinating conjunction following particles or genitival nouns in conditional statements, known as مَا الزَّائِدَة (mā z-zāʔida), 'superfluous mā'","examples":[{"text":"[…] وَلَا يَأْبَ ٱلشُّهَدَاءُ إِذَا مَا دُعُوا […]","english":"[…] And let not the witnesses refuse when they are called upon. […]"}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"loosely translates to that; introduces a verbal complement to a preposition, standing in place of the definite verbal noun","examples":[{"text":"وَلَهُمْ عَذَابٌ أَلِيمٌ بِمَا كَانُوا يَكْذِبُونَ","english":"And they will suffer a painful punishment, as they used to lie."},{"text":"أَتَظُنُّ أَنَّكَ بَعْدَ مَا أَحْرَقْتَنِي وَرَقَصْتَ كَٱلشَيْطَانِ فَوْقَ رُفَاتِي","english":"Do you think that, after you set me alight, and you danced like Satan over my ashes"}]},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"whenever"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"as far as, to the extent that, to the degree that"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"(oh) how...!","examples":[{"text":"مَا أَجْمَلَ ٱلْحَيَاةَ!","english":"How beautiful life is!"},{"text":"مَا أَلَذَّ ٱلطَّعَامَ!","english":"How delicious the food is!"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew מָה (ma) and Ugaritic 𐎎𐎅 (mh)."},"ipa":["/maː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43475","headword_ar":"مَا","root":"m","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"when following"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~","text_ar":"كُلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayona","text_ar":"اَيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~","text_ar":"اَىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", if having the signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY","text_ar":"الَّذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", is written separately. (El-Hareeree, in De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Ar., p. 67 of the Ar. text.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"added to certain adverbial nouns is not merely redundant, but gives to them a conditional and general signification; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayonamaA","text_ar":"اَيْنَمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wherever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayovumaA","text_ar":"حَيْثُمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wherever,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whenever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see Kur, ii. 143, 145, &c.: and see De Sacy's Gram., i. 537 and 538. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"While;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA dumotu Hay~FA","text_ar":"مَا دُمْتُ حَيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as much as;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see Kur, lxiv. 16. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA","text_ar":"بِمَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimaA kaAnuwA yafosuquwna","text_ar":"بِمَا كَانُوا يَفْسُقُونَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Because they did transgress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for that they did transgress."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kur.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aka maA waxayorFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّكَ مَا وَخَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa xayorK","text_ar":"مَعَ خَيْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayorN","text_ar":"خَيْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also added to a noun to denote the littleness of that which is signified by the noun; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arabN m~aA","text_ar":"اَرَبٌ مَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Some little want."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arb","text_ar":"ارب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA","text_ar":"اَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aA","text_ar":"اـِمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(of which latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aA laA","text_ar":"اـِمَّا لَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an instance) I have mentioned in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^am~aA","text_ar":"اَمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_im~aA","text_ar":"اـِمَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAligFA maA balaga","text_ar":"بَالِغًا مَا بَلَغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaga","text_ar":"بَلَغَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anota","text_ar":"مَا اَنْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What art thou?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what are thy qualities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attributes?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har, p. 155.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA rab~u AlEaAlamiyna","text_ar":"مَا رَبُّ العَالَمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, xxvi. 22, means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~N $aYo'K huwa","text_ar":"اَىٌّ شَىْءٍ هُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Jel.) See also an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faY~","text_ar":"فَىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA laka","text_ar":"مَا لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u $aYo'K","text_ar":"اَىُّ شَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vabata laka","text_ar":"ثَبَتَ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IbrD) and may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N m~aA","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ مَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Some particular thing: something."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyhi","text_ar":"اـِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) Also,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any particular thing?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IbrD.) See an ex. cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SabaAHN","text_ar":"صَبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatFY m~aA fulaAnN","text_ar":"فَتًى مَّا فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An excellent youth is such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IbrD.) See Kull, p. 336. See also Bd, middle p. 42. ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA daAma","text_ar":"مَا دَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA daAmuwA","text_ar":"مَا دَامُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As long as:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAZ~a","text_ar":"كَاظَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uroku","text_ar":"التُّرْكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jal~a","text_ar":"جَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~akolu A_ilaY AlT~uwli","text_ar":"الشَّكْلُ اـِلَى الطُّولِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA huwa","text_ar":"مَا هُوَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The form inclines somewhat to length;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with a rendering voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuqorN","text_ar":"عُقْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see De Sacy's Gr., sec. ed., i. 543 and 539: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N m~aA","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ مَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"above: in the Kur xxxviii. 23,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"is redundant, (Bd,) denoting vagueness and wonder, (Ksh, Bd,) or a corroborative of fewness: (Jel:) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether great or little in degree or importance.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", the negative particle, followed by a pret., often requires the latter to be rendered in English by the preterperfect: ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotuhu mu*o yawomaAn","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُهُ مُذْ يَوْمَان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not seen him for two days."},{"kind":"text","text":"See De Sacy's Anthol. Gram. Ar., p. 253."}],"source_refs":["IbrD","Bd","Ksh","Jel"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}